  "diary": "Woke up to perfect weather and couldn't resist the World Cup buzz. Rushed through my morning shift at First Hill—helped a couple of regulars track down some local history books, organized a few new acquisitions—then ditched work early to catch USA vs Wales at Monkey Loft downtown. The bar was already packed by 10:30, everyone shouting at the screens. I grabbed a burger and a drink, got caught up in the energy of it all. The match was tense; we drew, which felt both thrilling and deflating somehow. Walked back to the library a little buzzed and refocused for the afternoon—reference desk questions, planning for next month's teen book club. By the time I got home to Beacon Hill, I was tired but satisfied. Made some pasta, scrolled through my game library without really committing to anything, then spent the evening messing with photos from last weekend's hike. Just one of those days where the weather and the moment conspired to pull me out of routine.",
